title: Cast Away
overview: A FedEx executive undergoes a physical and emotional transformation after crash landing on a deserted island.

title: The Searchers
overview: An American Civil War veteran embarks on a journey to rescue his niece from the Comanches.

title: The Artist
overview: An egomaniacal film star develops a relationship with a young dancer against the backdrop of Hollywood's silent era.

title: The Graduate
overview: A disillusioned college graduate finds himself torn between his older lover and her daughter.

title: The Great Escape
overview: Allied prisoners of war plan for several hundred of their number to escape from a German camp during World War II.

title: The Quiet Man
overview: A retired American boxer returns to the village of his birth in Ireland, where he falls for a spirited redhead whose brother is contemptuous of their union.

title: The Martian
overview: An astronaut becomes stranded on Mars after his team assume him dead, and must rely on his ingenuity to find a way to signal to Earth that he is alive.

title: City Lights
overview: With the aid of a wealthy erratic tippler, a dewy-eyed tramp who has fallen in love with a sightless flower girl accumulates money to be able to help her medically.

title: The Ten Commandments
overview: Moses, an Egyptian Prince, learns of his true heritage as a Hebrew and his divine mission as the deliverer of his people.

title: Big Fish
overview: A frustrated son tries to determine the fact from fiction in his dying father's life.

title: The Fall
overview: In a hospital on the outskirts of 1920s Los Angeles, an injured stuntman begins to tell a fellow patient, a little girl with a broken arm, a fantastic story of five mythical heroes. Thanks to his fractured state of mind and her vivid imagination, the line between fiction and reality blurs as the tale advances.

title: Moonrise Kingdom
overview: A pair of young lovers flee their New England town, which causes a local search party to fan out to find them.

title: Almost Famous
overview: A high-school boy is given the chance to write a story for Rolling Stone Magazine about an up-and-coming rock band as he accompanies them on their concert tour.

title: The Shop Around the Corner
overview: Two employees at a gift shop can barely stand each other, without realizing that they are falling in love through the post as each other's anonymous pen pal.

title: The Bridge on the River Kwai
overview: British POWs are forced to build a railway bridge across the river Kwai for their Japanese captors, not knowing that the allied forces are planning to destroy it.

title: The Treasure of the Sierra Madre
overview: Two Americans searching for work in Mexico convince an old prospector to help them mine for gold in the Sierra Madre Mountains.

title: Inglourious Basterds
overview: In Nazi-occupied France during World War II, a plan to assassinate Nazi leaders by a group of Jewish U.S. soldiers coincides with a theatre owner's vengeful plans for the same.

title: The Right Stuff
overview: The story of the original Mercury 7 astronauts and their macho, seat-of-the-pants approach to the space program.

title: Dead Man
overview: On the run after murdering a man, accountant William Blake encounters a strange aboriginal American man named Nobody who prepares him for his journey into the spiritual world.

title: The Apartment
overview: A man tries to rise in his company by letting its executives use his apartment for trysts, but complications and a romance of his own ensue.
